**7.**

$$ f(x) = -3x^2 + 6x + 3 $$

Find the vertex.

$$ \left(-\frac{(6)}{2(-3)}, f\left(-\frac{(6)}{2(-3)}\right)\right) $$

$$ (1, f(1)) $$

$$ f(1) = -3(1)^2 + 6(1) + 3 $$

$$ f(1) = -3(1) + 6 + 3 $$

$$ f(1) = -3 + 6 + 3 $$

$$ f(1) = 6 $$

$$ (1, 6) $$

