$$ 0 = -3x^2 + 6x + 3 $$

$$ 0 = -3(x^2 - 2x - 1) $$

$$ 0 = x^2 - 2x - 1 $$

$$ x = \frac{-(-2) \pm \sqrt{(-2)^2 - 4(1)(-1)}}{2(1)} $$

$$ x = \frac{2 \pm 2\sqrt{2}}{2} $$

$$ x = 1 \pm \sqrt{2} $$

$$ (1 + \sqrt{2}, 0), (1 - \sqrt{2}, 0) $$

$$ (2,4142, 0), (-0.4142, 0) $$

Find one point on either side of the vertex.

$$ f(2) = -3(2)^2 + 6(2) + 3 $$

$$ f(2) = -3(4) + 12 + 3 $$

$$ f(2) = -12 + 12 + 3 $$

