Find the vertex.

$$ \left(-\frac{(16)}{2(4)}, f\left(-\frac{(16)}{2(4)}\right)\right) $$

$$ (-2, f(-2)) $$

$$ f(-2) = 4(-2)^2 + 16(-2) $$

$$ f(-2) = 4(4) - 32 $$

$$ f(-2) = 16 - 32 $$

$$ f(-2) = -16 $$

$$ (-2, -16) $$

Find the $y$-intercept.

$$ f(0) = 4(0)^2 + 16(0) $$

$$ f(0) = 0 $$

$$ (0, 0) $$

Find the $x$-intercepts (if any).

$$ 0 = 4x^2 + 16x $$

$$ 0 = x^2 + 4x $$

$$ 0 = x(x + 4)$$

$$ (0, 0), (-4, 0) $$

Find one point on either side of the vertex.

$$ f(-8) = 4(-8)^2 + 16(-8) $$

$$ f(-8) = 4(64) - 128 $$

$$ f(-8) = 256 - 128 $$

$$ f(-8) = 128 $$

$$ (-8, 128) $$

